<TITLE> Mother, daughter crushed by speeding truck </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Rajbari, Apr 06 (bdnews24.com)  A mother and daughter have died and another family member injured when they were crushed by a truck at Bangladesh Hat on Rajbari-Kushtia high way on Tuesday at around midday. After the accident people in a frenzy burnt the truck and blocked the road for an hour. The dead are Jolekha, 30, and her daughter Tuktuki, 6 of Bara Chaubaria village under Mirat Union of Pangsha upazila. The injured man, Liton, is Jolekha's niece. Liton was hospitalized in a critical situation at Faridpur Medical College. Aminul Islam, the sub-inspector Pangsha Thana told bdnews24.com that the three were returning from a relative's house of Boalia in a van. He said that a truck, driving at speed, hit the van from behind. The police and fire brigade team, on being informed of the accident, came to the spot and took control of the situation. But the driver and his helper managed to flee, he said. bdnew
